  "event_preview": "Las Vegas Motor Speedway is a 1.500-mile (2.414 km) tri-oval intermediate speedway in Paradise, Nevada — one of the fastest and most high-banked tracks in the NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series. The LiUNA! has been held at this venue since 1997, traditionally serving as one of the first five races of the season, and this year marks the 29th running of the event. The 20-degree banking in the turns — increased during the 2006 repave — produces multiple racing grooves and sustains high side-by-side speeds throughout the run. The defending race winner is Justin Allgaier, who dominated last year's edition for JR Motorsports, leading a race-high 102 laps to claim his 26th career O'Reilly Series victory.",
